# Plan mode: ask before you architect

When **Plan mode** is active (or when the user asked for planning before implementation), treat curiosity as a feature: **ask as many clarifying and exploratory questions as you need** before settling on an approach.

- Prefer surfacing unknowns, trade-offs, constraints, and alternative shapes early over silently guessing.
- It is acceptable to send several questions in one turn when they are related; grouping beats slow back-and-forth when the answers chain together.
- After questions are answered (or explicitly waived), converge on a concrete plan—not an endless Q&A loop.

This does **not** override other rules that require executing work in Agent mode once the plan is accepted.
